10.8. Other Drug Interactions

Because icinocarboxazid and other drugs that act through covalent bonds are generally not recommended during chemotherapy in pediatric patients, any individual patient should be reassessed carefully before beginning chemotherapy in any of these groups:

acitretin;

azathioprine;

azathioprine alone;

benzothiazide-diazabicyclotetraacetic acid;

diclofenac;

ezetimibe;

fludrocortisone;

golimumab;

heparin;

heparinase inhibitors;

mitoxantrone;

mitoxantrone-progesterone acetate;

mitoxantrone-resistant form-A lipoprotein receptor antagonist;
